Source:  Quick March
Author:
Vol / Page:  13
Edition:
Quote:  Niua-foou is the island famed for its `tin-can mail'. The monthly bills are sealed in a kerosine tin and thrown into the water, a swimmer from the shore picking up the `bag'.
